product.name: 【SG】 Gateron KS-9 Mechanical Keyboard Switch
product.description:
Local SG Seller – Fast Delivery – Buy with Confidence!
Note: Not compatible with Outemu hot-swap PCB (e.g. Tecware Phantom RGB), as it has a narrower socket that only accept Outemu switches.
Minimum order 30 pcs, can mix and match.
Contact us if you would like to have switch tester kit with 9 type of Gateron switches.
【Gateron White Switch】
Type: Linear
Actuation Force: 35 gf
Actuation Distance: 2.0 mm
Travel Distance: 4.0 mm
Description: The white switch has the lightest actuation force amongst the linear switches. The smooth nature of the Gateron allows it to be triggered with very light force, making it effortless to type.
【Gateron Red Switch】
Type: Linear
Actuation Force: 45 gf
Actuation Distance: 2.0 mm
Travel Distance: 4.0 mm
Description: Gateron red is the most commonly used Gateron switch because it is a linear switch, making the typing sound quieter. The pressure is more moderate, light, and prolonged periods of typing will not feel tired.
【Gateron Yellow Switch】
Type: Linear
Actuation Force: 50 gf
Actuation Distance: 2.0 mm
Travel Distance: 4.0 mm
Description: The design of the Gateron yellow switch is the same as the red switch, but the departure strength is 5g bigger, which seems small but does offer a difference in feeling. The feedback of the yellow switch is more rigid, but it doesn’t need heavy force to be triggered.
【Gateron Black Switch】
Type: Linear
Actuation Force: 60 gf
Actuation Distance: 2.0 mm
Travel Distance: 4.0 mm
Description: The black switch is a linear switch with the greatest strength amongst standard mass-produced switches. Those who like mechanical keyboards with a stronger trigger force will likely prefer the Gateron black switch.
【Gateron Brown Switch】
Type: Tactile
Actuation Force: 55 gf
Actuation Distance: 2.0 mm
Travel Distance: 4.0 mm
Description: Gateron brown switch has the characteristics of both the red and blue switches. The vertical press still feels smooth, but also has the feeling of a bump. The sound is relatively quiet and will not disturb the surrounding environment.
【Gateron Blue Switch】
Type: Clicky
Actuation Force: 60 gf
Actuation Distance: 2.3 mm
Travel Distance: 4.0 mm
Description: Gateron Blue has a unique clicky touch feel and a louder sound. It still has the characteristics of the Gateron Switch and is smooth with tactile feedback. This structure can let you type for a long period and not get tired. It’s ideal for games and typing.
【Gateron Green Switch】
Type: Clicky
Actuation Force: 80 gf
Actuation Distance: 2.3 mm
Travel Distance: 4.0 mm
Description: Gateron Green switch is seen by many as an upgraded version of Gateron Blue switch. 80g of press force is 20g higher than the Blue switch. The green switch has stronger feedback and a harder rebound.
